INTRODUCTION

II

From the Anukramanik─Бdhy─Бya of the Adi Parvan, it will be observed that, according to the Southern Recension, the Udyoga Parvan should consist of 186 chapters and 7998 stanzas according to two manuscripts and 6998 stanzas according to two other manuscripts, whereas, according to the Northern Recension, the number of chapters remains the same, though the number of stanzas need be only 6698. (See the Tables appended to the Introductions to Vols. I & II and page 62 of Vol. I). No single manuscript that has been used for the printing of the Southern Recension divides the Udyoga Parvan into exactly 186 chapters. But the Grantha Edition of the text, published about 1895, from Sarabhojir─Бjaparam, Tanjore, divides the text into exactly 186 chapters. In the division of chapters for the Principal Text printed for the Southern Recension, the Grantha Edition has, in the main, been followed, wherever feasible. Thus, the number of chapters for the Southern Recension has been made to approximate closely to that given in the Anukramaс╣Зik─Бdhy─Бya of the Adi Parvan. We have shown in appropriate places in the body of the Text, the deviations of the several Manuscripts in their scheme of chapters, wherever they occur. However, to illustrate the divergences at a

INTRODUCTION

glance, a Concordance exhibiting the scheme of chapters in the Northern Recension, according to the Poona Edition with Bhavadipa, the Mixed Recension, according to the Kumbakonam edition and the Southern Recension according to the Text printed herein, is appended.

The actual number of stanzas in all the 186 chapters, according to the Principal Text edited, comes however to 6667┬╜ stanzas only.

INTRODUCTION

III

Attention is invited to the foot-note on page 314 of the Text. It will be observed that the 44th chapter of the Southern Recension, though found in all the Recensions, is conspicuous by its omission by Sri Sankarac─Бrya in his Bh─Бс╣гya on the Sanatsuj─Бtiya. It is evident that, according to Sri Sankara, this chapter did not form part of the Sanatsuj─Бtiya. But V─Бdir─Бja comments on this chapter in his Lakс╣г─Бlank─Бra and all the Manuscripts of the Southern Recension contain this chapter. In the Descriptive Catalogue of Sanskrit Manuscripts of the Tanjore Palace Library, Vol XII, No. 7381 represents a Manuscript of the Sanatsuj─Бtiyabhagya of Sri Sankara wherein the above chapter is stated to be commented on by Sri Sankara But a careful examination of the Bh─Бс╣гya reveals the fact that herein the scribe has written Sarvaj├▒an─Бr─Бyana’s Bh─Бrat─Бrthaprak─Бsa on this chapter and passed it off in the colophon as the Bhasya of Sri Sankara. We have not, so far, come across any genuine Bhasya of Sri Sankara on this chapter.

INTRODUCTION

IV

In the Parvasangrah─Бdhy─Бya of the Adi Parvan, there is mention ofрд╡реНрдпрд╛рд╕рд╛рднрд┐рдЧрдордирдкрд░реНрд╡as an internal parvan of the Udyoga Parvan. But in all the printed texts so far published, this has been styled as the рдпрд╛рдирд╕рдиреНрдзрд┐рдкрд░реНрд╡ and notas as **рд╡реНрдпрд╛рд╕рд╛рднрд┐рдЧрдордирдкрд░реНрд╡,**We have, however, styled it рд╡реНрдпрд╛рд╕рд╛рднрд┐рдЧрдордирдкрд░реНрд╡, if only to be in conformity with the name given to it in the Adi Parvan of the Southern Recension.

Chapters 127 to 137 of the Southern Recension have hitherto been printed in all the editions as part of theрднрдЧрд╡рджреНрдпрд╛рдирдкрд░реНрд╡ whereas these should really be called **рд╡рд┐рд╡рд╛рджрдкрд░реНрд╡тАФ**the name given to them in the Parvasangrahadhy─Бya, according to all Recensions. We have, accordingly, printed these chapters as рд╡рд┐рд╡рд╛рджрдкрд░реНрд╡.

Chapters 141 to 145 of the Southern Recension have hitherto been printed in all the editions as part of the рд╕реИрдиреНрдпрдирд┐рд░реНрдпрд╛рдгрдкрд░реНрд╡,whereas they should really be calledрднреАрд╖реНрдорд╛рднрд┐рд╖реЗрдЪрдирдкрд░реНрд╡тАФthe name given to them in the Parvasangrah─Бdhy─Бya, according to all the Recensions. We have, therefore, printed these as рднреАрд╖реНрдорд╛рднрд┐рд╖реЗрдЪрдирдкрд░реНрд╡. It will be observed that the proper sequence is for рднреАрд╖реНрдорд╛рднрд┐рд╖реЗрдЪрдирдкрд░реНрд╡ to follow the рд╕рдиреНрдпрдирд┐рд░реНрдпрд╛рдгрдкрд░реНрд╡ and not to precede it as has been wrongly made out in page 49 of Vol. I of the Mahabharata (Adi Parvan-Southern Recension).
